e stabilization phase and must undergo a qualitative test every 45 days for one year.(c) Following this, the patient moves into the maintenance phase and must undergo a qualitative test every six months thereafter.(d) At any point the provider wants to assess compliance, the patient must be willing to produce a qualitative or quantitative test upon the provider request.NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to describe the progression of treatment for substance use disorder.Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law and underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone: